3. Insurance-Specific Use Cases: Customer Enrollment Optimization and Beyond
Customer Enrollment Use Case:
•	Member months by product line (medical, dental, vision, pharmacy, life) — enabling enrollment trend analysis.
•	Current plan tenure and lifetime member months — identifying at-risk members for retention.
•	Study period windowing — each member's data computed per rolling study period with current study period and snapshot flags.
•	LOB mapping validated against finance reports (99% accuracy) — ensuring enrollment counts match financial reporting.
•	Multi-product indicators (dental, vision, pharmacy, life flags) — enabling cross-sell/upsell analysis.

Stop-Loss & Cost Prediction:
The cost module computes FIP/FOP/Professional/Rx costs with allowed amounts, PMPM normalization, and expenditure percentages. Combined with DXCG prospective risk scores, this directly feeds models to predict members likely to exceed stop-loss thresholds.

High-Risk Case Management (HRCM):
31 ACHCC clinical condition categories + concurrent/prospective risk scores + care management indicators (9 program enrollment flags) enable identification of members with the highest utilization.

Health Equity & BISG:
A production BISG module uses census surname data, first-name probability data, and census block-group demographics to impute race/ethnicity with posterior probabilities across 6 categories. Integrated with SVI and ADI indices.

Medication Adherence:
PDC (Proportion of Days Covered) calculations for 6 chronic drug classes with an 80% adherence threshold flag — supporting quality measures and care gap identification.

